cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on compressing RNN acoustic models for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing, both of which are sub-areas of cs.CL.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a technique for compressing RNNs, which is a machine learning model. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed technique in terms of accuracy, which is a common evaluation metric in machine learning.
3. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with acoustic modeling for speech recognition, which involves processing and analyzing sound signals. This falls under the domain of cs.SD, which deals with sound and music computing.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a technique for compressing RNNs, which is a type of artificial neural network. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed technique in terms of accuracy, which is a common evaluation metric in AI.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the goal of building compact and accurate speech recognition systems which can be run efficiently on mobile devices. This involves designing and optimizing control systems for efficient operation, which falls under the domain of cs.SY.
